<TITLE> Hoax call to Zardari put Pakistan on high alert </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ISLAMABAD, Dec 6 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Nuclear-armed Pakistan put its forces on high alert after a hoax caller pretending to be India's foreign minister spoke to President Asif Ali Zardari in a threatening manner on Nov. 28, two days after the attacks on Mumbai began, Pakistan's Dawn newspaper reported on Saturday. "It's true," a diplomat with knowledge of the exchanges told Reuters when asked whether the newspaper report was correct
